2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper examines the relationship between concept recognition and decision making in CNNs. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with the decision-making process of a neural network. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the paper uses natural language to describe the input concepts and their relationship to CNN decisions. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the behavior of a neural network.
